  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Culture of Peace and GBV</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">- Assesment on violence in 22 communities being supported by project &quot;Comunidades preparadas ante la Vulnerablilidad,&quot; which will serve as a baseline
- Systematization of MCM work with young people
- Update MCM Gender Policy, to be disseminated with project beneficiaries
- Masculinities workshops
- Municipal forum on gender-based violence</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Project addition designed to coincide with current MCM project &quot;Comunidades preparadas ante la Vulnerablilidad,&quot; combining Christian Aid two regional programmes.  22 youth and women&apos;s community groups (main beneficiaries of project) will participate in additional processes to address gender-based violence (tackling violence, building peace).  Project will specifically address how disaster (climate change) differs in its effects, according to gender.  Project will also extend gender sensitvity programming being supported by CAID to include wider participation from MCM base.</narrative>
  </description>
